BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:AaTAsoVjL9IWrzGG5G_ra
SUMMARY:Figure/Ground: New Criteria
DTSTAMP:20260322T034733Z
DTSTART:20260329T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Figure/Ground: New Criteria is inspired by cultural historian S
	arah Lewis’s concept of “groundwork aesthetics\,” exploring figure-ground 
	relationships and their connection to social tension. It builds on Lewis’s
	 work\, which—set against the expansion of Stand Your Ground laws across t
	he United States since 2005\, laws that broadly define rights to use letha
	l self-defense against perceived threats—describes a range of artistic int
	erventions that reimagine “the literal and figurative meaning of ground.” 
	Primarily featuring works from the Henry collection created in the twenty-
	first century\, Figure/Ground reflects a period in which hard-won civil ri
	ghts and claims to self-determination have been eroded across the US\, dis
	proportionately affecting Black\, Brown\, LGBTQ\\+\, and other marginalize
	d communities.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-gro
	und-new-criteria/17923441/2026-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-ground-new-criteri
	a/17923441/2026-03-29T00
LOCATION:Henry Art Gallery\, 15th Ave NE & 41st St\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EWyAvGpp_G9ygoCN7_CJK
SUMMARY:Beyond Mysticism: The Modern Northwest
DTSTAMP:20260322T034733Z
DTSTART:20260329T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:image: Drift No. 2\, 1936\, Malcolm M. Roberts\, American\, 191
	3-1990\, tempera on board\, 25 1/2 x 20 5/8 in.\, Seattle Art Museum\, Eug
	ene Fuller Memorial Collection\, 37.103\, © Malcolm M. Roberts\, photo: Sc
	ott Leen.\n\nInspired by the region’s natural beauty and rapidly changing 
	city\, this exhibition showcases artists who told the raw story of Seattle
	 in the 20th century. By sharing the Pacific Northwest’s perspective throu
	gh trending art styles—including Social Realism\, Surrealism\, and Abstrac
	t Expressionism—these artists offered a unique take on Modernist art and c
	hallenged the “mystic” label ascribed to their works.\n\nSpearheading the 
	movement were local icons Mark Tobey\, Kenneth Callahan\, Guy Anderson\, a
	nd Morris Graves—but the range and breadth of Pacific Northwest art goes b
	eyond the “Big Four” of the Northwest School. Featuring more than 150 piec
	es\, this exhibition showcases works that investigate the complexities of 
	daily life in the region. Whether applying an ecocritical lens or producin
	g dreamy and uncanny visuals\, these artists expressed the duality of the 
	natural world and city life to warn of the environmental and social impact
	s of industrialization.\n\nFrom Malcolm Roberts to Kenjiro Nomura\, learn 
	how Northwest artists applied their regional perspective to broader artist
	ic developments to create a new form of American Modernism.\n\nThe exhibit
	ion is accompanied by a fully illustrated catalogue authored by Theresa Pa
	panikolas\, SAM’s Ann M. Barwick Curator of American Art.\n\nhttps://seato
	day.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-modern-northwest/183
	08126/2026-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-mode
	rn-northwest/18308126/2026-03-29T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:P7br-OUhj3oLRw-3qc28K
SUMMARY:PCC Cooking Class - Savory Sichuan
DTSTAMP:20260322T034733Z
DTSTART:20260329T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn to make traditional Chinese dishes at home! In this cooki
	ng class\, you’ll pick up techniques and tips for capturing the flavors of
	 Sichuan cuisine. Get practice infusing oil with chilis and hand-grinding 
	spices for a sauce as you create deeply flavorful dan dan noodles. You’ll 
	also try your hand at methodically rolling and flattening dough with scall
	ions for savory pancakes\, which you’ll pair with a scratch-made dipping s
	auce. By the end of class\, you’ll be ready to recreate the entire menu in
	 your kitchen. \n\nContains pork and dairy. \n\nAbout the instructor: Our 
	seasoned instructors and chefs have been chosen to be a part of PCC Cooks 
	because of their culinary expertise and sincere enthusiasm and talent for 
	teaching. \n\nThis is a hands-on format class for adults. \n\n This cookin
	g class is available at multiple PCC locations and dates. See below for de
	tails: \n\nBellevue PCC \n\n-Friday\, March 27\, 6:00 - 8:00 pm \n\n-Sunda
	y\, March 29\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm \n\n-Friday\, April 3\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm \
	n\nBothell PCC \n\n-Friday\, March 27\, 6:00 - 8:00 pm \n\n-Sunday\, March
	 29\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm \n\nBurien PCC \n\n-Sunday\, March 29\, 10:00 - 12:
	00 pm \n\nColumbia City PCC \n\n-Sunday\, March 29\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm \n\n
	Edmonds PCC \n\n-Friday\, March 27\, 6:00 - 8:00 pm \n\n-Sunday\, March 29
	\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm \n\nGreen Lake Village PCC \n\n-Friday\, March 27\, 6:
	00 - 8:00 pm \n\n-Sunday\, March 29\, 10:00 - 12:00 pm\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pcc-cooking-class-savory-sichuan/18296264/20
	26-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pcc-cooking-class-savory-
	sichuan/18296264/2026-03-29T00
LOCATION:Columbia City PCC\, 3610 S Edmunds St\, Seattle\, WA
